                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/16549.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Torreon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-10-22T18:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 22, 1915—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Recognition of this Government last night and today by Argentina, Brazil,
                    Bolivia, Colombia,<note n="52" xml:id="d1010fn52">This is probably a mistake
                        made in transmission, and should read “Chile”—one of the six governments
                        represented at the conference. Colombia had already recognized the de facto
                        Government, on October 19 (File No. 812.00/16528).</note> Uruguay,
                    Guatemala. Today upon personal invitation Generals Carranza and Obregon reviewed
                    about 20,000 troops of General Obregon. Prior to review General Obregon received
                    news fall of Guaymas, last port held by Villa.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">J. W. Belt.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
